'''Necile''' is a [[Dryad|wood nymph]] who becomes the adoptive mother of [[Santa Claus]] in the 1902 novel [[The Life and Adventures of Santa Claus]].<ref>{{cite web |work=[[ComicsAlliance]] |url=http://comicsalliance.com/ask-chris-87-the-santa-claus-of-two-worlds/ |title=The Santa Claus of Two Worlds |date=26 December 2014 |first=Chris |last=Sims |quote=Shiegra knows better than to cross Ak, however, and she gives Li’l Claus her milk until a wood nymph named Necile decides that she wants to raise Santa as her son, since immortals have no children of their own.}}</ref>
She recurs in the [[The Life and Adventures of Santa Claus (1985 film)|1985 film]] by [[Rankin/Bass]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uproxx.com/tv/rankin-bass-top-10-craziness/ |work=[[Uproxx]] |quote=Ak decides that was a dumb idea and has wood nymph Necile and a random assortment of freaky forest creatures raise him instead. |title=Ridiculous Rudolph: A Merry Ranking Of The 10 Craziest Rankin-Bass Holiday Specials |first=Nathan |last=Birch |date=21 December 2015}}</ref> (voiced by Lesley Miller) then the [[Shounen Santa no Daibouken|1996 anime series]] then the [[The Life & Adventures of Santa Claus (2000 film)|2000 film]] by [[Mike Young Productions]] (voiced by [[Dixie Carter]]) inspired by the novel.
She has also been portrayed in musicals adapting the story.<ref>{{cite web |work=[[Leader-Post]] |first=Annie |last=McLeod |title= RLT pulls back the curtain to reveal the man that is Santa Claus |date=24 November 2016 |url=http://leaderpost.com/entertainment/local-arts/rlt-pulls-back-the-curtain-to-reveal-the-man-that-is-santa-claus |quote=Claus was a mortal baby that was found in the woods by a nymph named Necile. He was named Neclaus, but Necile preferred to call him Claus, and she raised him on her own. In this world, which includes the likes of woodland fairies and elves, the inhabitants are immortal. As he grows up, Necile warns Claus of the Awgwas}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://newtownbee.com/newtown-resident-cast-in-new-holiday-musical/ |title=Newtown Resident Cast In New Holiday Musical |date=30 November 2016 |quote=Shearin will play Necile, a mythical being who discovers Claus as a baby and watches over him throughout his life.}}</ref>
