'''Roger-Émile Aubry''', [[C.Ss.R.]], (11 April 1923 – 17 February 2010) was the [[Roman Catholic]] bishop of the [[Vicariate Apostolic of Reyes]], [[Bolivia]].<ref>{{Catholic-hierarchy|diocese|dreyes||23 January 2015}}</ref>

Ordained to the priesthood on 24 February 1949, [[Pope Paul VI]] appointed Aubry bishop of the Reyes vicariate apostolic on 14 July 1973 and he was ordained on 16 September 1973 retiring on 1 May 1999.<ref>{{Catholic-hierarchy|bishop|baubry|Bishop Roger-Émile Aubry, C.SS.R.|23 January 2015}}</ref>

